      <body>
         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">Melbourne, ¶ 8 May 1889 ¶ H. Moors Esqr ¶ Under Secretary. ¶ Sir...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">89.05.08</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">To Henry Moors</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">M89/6077, unit 431, VPRS 3992/P inward registered correspondence, VA 475 Chief Secretary's Department, Public Record Office, Victoria.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">Melbourne,</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">8 May 1889</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">H. Moors Esqr</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">Under Secretary.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">Sir</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Having now learnt, that my proposition, made on the 30th March<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn0" n="1">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>M to A. Deakin, 30 March 1889.</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>for the promotion of some of the officers in the Gov. Botanists Department, cannot be carried out under the Public Service Act,<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn1" n="2">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>See notes with M to A. Deakin, 30 March 1889.</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>I have now the honor to withdraw the estimates for 1889-1890, submitted previously, and to substitute two others, one framed quite in accordance with former estimates, and one so formed, as to afford the following improvements in the position of Officers in this establishment, vize:</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Mr Charles French, sen.,<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn2" n="3">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Charles French Snr. [Standard disambiguation note added for ease of retrieval in searches.]</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>first herbarium-assistant (non-clerical), whose maximum pay I would respectfully recommend, to be raised from £252.-.-<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>to £300.-.-, whereby an additional increment of four pounds would be gained annually by him.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Mr James Minchin, second herbarium-assistant<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>(non-clerical),<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>whose maximum pay a year I would beg to be raised from £132.-.-<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>to £180.-.-<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>whereby he would receive an increment of £8.-.-<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>a<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>year.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I further beg to point out, that with the ever increasing office obligations in so rising a colony like ours it would be most desirable, that the item for books, instruments, botanic collections, seeds, travelling and incidental expenses be increased by £110.-.-, to provide thus also for payment of temporary assistance and overtime work, it being impossible — even with the strictest exercise of economy — to carry out satisfactorily all branches of the service here with the formerly allotted item for these particular purposes.<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn3" n="4">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>On 10 May 1889,<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>Moors minuted that he had withdrawn M's estimates, summarizing<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>the pay increases M proposed and adding: 'This of course will have to receive the sanction of the Public Service Board'.<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     </p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
            </p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">I have the honor to be,</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Sir, your obedient servant</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Ferd. von Mueller,</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Gov. Botanist.</p>
         </div>
